        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 1:13PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 113 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Burro Flats, moving south at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Alamogordo, Burro Flats, High Rolls, La Luz, Mountain Park, and Karr
Canyon.

This includes Highway 54 in New Mexico near mile marker 70.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
